comments.body:
I think this snippet of code could be documented in the following fashion

```
// If we receive many `SENDTXRCNCL` from the same peer, before to receive a
// single `VERACK`, re-register the peer id state with potentially different local
// and remote salts.
```

As far as I can see, at `SENDTXRCNCL` reception we do not check for duplicate `SENDTXRCNCL` message (we check if we have txreconciliation enabled, then that its happening before verack reception and then that transaction-relay is enabled on the link) and we can call `RegisterPeer` multiple times.

